      {
        "id": 1823656,
        "name": "Nolan E",
        "username": "Nolan_E",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/nolan_e/{size}/1426_2.png",
        "created_at": "2015-12-30T01:42:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>There\u2019s not much of a diurnal swing so the wines from central and south Texas tend to be flabby and soft.</p>\n<p>There are some really good wines made in the northern part of the state (McPherson) but I haven\u2019t had luck with central Texas wines.</p>\n<p>That being said, there are lots of wineries that don\u2019t distribute and I had no experience with while in Houston.</p>",
